hps.usecase3.title.message: Calculate the time to receive output from the model
hps.usecase1.desc.message: You can easily set the methodology and number of times to search. Then, the HPS will find the value you want on its own.
hps.usecase2.desc.message: If the merge ratio is set as the target parameter, HPS searches for the optimal merge ratio.
hps.usecase3.desc.message: By using the parameters used for preprocessing as input, you can find the time required for model output.
job.emptycase.desc.message: Input a bunch of parameters you want to experiment with. after that, Jonathan Flightbase's JOB will run them sequentially.
job.usecase1.title.message: Experiment a large batch-size model with Multi-GPU
job.usecase2.title.message: Experiment with various datasets or codes at once
job.usecase1.desc.message: Models that require large batch size utilize the multi-GPU function to secure large memory.
job.usecase2.desc.message: If there are various versions of the dataset or code, set it as a parameter and create multiple jobs.
job.usecase3.desc.message: Focus on more important issues while FlightBase tries to find the best results for you.
